data.content:
You'll hit **four obsoletion warnings** (all errors if `TreatWarningsAsErrors` is on):

| Warning | API | Fix |
|---------|-----|-----|
| **SYSLIB0058** | `SslStream.KeyExchangeAlgorithm`, `.CipherAlgorithm`, `.HashAlgorithm` (and `*Strength` properties) | Use `SslStream.NegotiatedCipherSuite` instead. Preserve any cipher-validation logic using the new enum. |
| **SYSLIB0059** | `SystemEvents.EventsThreadShutdown` | Register on `AppDomain.ProcessExit` instead. |
| **SYSLIB0061** | `Queryable.MaxBy` overload taking `IComparer<TSource>` | Switch to the overload that takes `IComparer<TKey>` (comparer over the *key*, not the source element). |
| **SYSLIB0062** | `XsltSettings.EnableScript = true` | XSLT script execution is obsoleted with no built-in replacement. Suppress the warning if you accept the risk, or refactor transforms to avoid embedded script. |

**Example fix for SYSLIB0058:**
```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
logger.Log($"Cipher: {sslStream.CipherAlgorithm} ({sslStream.CipherStrength})");

// After (.NET 10)
logger.Log($"CipherSuite: {sslStream.NegotiatedCipherSuite}");
```

**Example fix for SYSLIB0059:**
```csharp
// Before
SystemEvents.EventsThreadShutdown += OnCleanup;

// After
AppDomain.CurrentDomain.ProcessExit += (s, e) => OnCleanup(s, e);
```

All four are **obsoletion warnings** (not errors by default), so the build will still succeed unless you have `<TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>`.
